quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  98,1,Those who disbelieved among people of the book and the polytheists were not to disengage (from their ideas) until the clear proof came to them
  98,2,a messenger from God reading purified scriptures
  98,3,with true (and lasting) writings in it
  98,4,And those who were given the book did not become divided until after the clear proof had come to them
  98,5,"And they were only ordered to serve God, being sincere to Him in the way of life (religion) as a monotheist, and perform the mandatory prayers and give the mandatory charity. And that is the lasting religion"
  98,6,"Indeed those who disbelieved among people of the book and the polytheists will be in fire of hell, remaining in there forever. They are worst of the creatures"
  98,7,"Those who believed and did good works, they are best of the creatures"
  98,8,"Their reward with their Master is eternal gardens which rivers flow through them, remaining in there forever and ever. God is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him. That is for anyone who fears his Master"